<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900703-0057</DOCNO><DOCID>900703-0057.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Energy Conversion Devices Inc.:   Alliance Is Set With Canon   To Build Solar Cells in U.S.</HL><DATE>07/03/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ENER CANNY WNEWS</CO><LP>   Energy Conversion Devices Inc., Troy Mich., said it hasagreed to form a joint venture with Canon Inc. of Japan tomanufacture solar cells in the U.S.   Canon is making an initial $30 million capitalcontribution to the joint venture, including a credit of $8million for canceling a term loan to Energy ConversionDevices. Energy Conversion Devices is contributing its solarmanufacturing plant and a technology license.</LP><TEXT>   Eliichi Kondo, chief executive of Canon's chemicalproducts operations, will be president and chief executiveofficer of the joint venture.</TEXT></DOC>